<dicta xmlns="http://www.sibawayhi.org/schema/2024/05/igt" bab="038">
   <dictum id="٤٠٨٧٢">
      <text>
         <ar>يَا سَاْرِقَ اللَّيْلَةِ أَهْلَ الدَّاْرِ</ar>
         <free>O <ed>you</ed>-robbing[acc] <ed>of</ed> the night[gen]
         <ed>the</ed> folk[acc]
         <ed>of</ed> the house[gen]</free>
      </text>
      <igt>
         <t>
            <ar>يَا</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>سَاْرِقَ</ar>
            <xlit>sāriq<infla/></xlit>
            <en>robber</en>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>اللَّيْلَةِ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>أَهْلَ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>الدَّاْرِ</ar>
         </t>
      </igt>
   </dictum>
   <dictum id="٥٨٠٢٢">
      <text>
         <ar>سَرَقْتُ اللَّيْلَةَ أَهْلَ الدَّاْرِ</ar>
         <free>I robbed the night[acc] the folk[acc]
         of the house[gen]</free>
         <alt>I robbed tonight[acc] the folk[acc]
         of the house[gen]</alt>
      </text>
      <igt>
         <t>
            <ar>سَرَقْتُ</ar>
            <xlit>saraq-tu</xlit>
            <en>I roobed</en>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>اللَّيْلَةَ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>أَهْلَ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>الدَّاْرِ</ar>
         </t>
      </igt>
   </dictum>
   <dictum id="٤٦٧٦٧">
      <text>
         <ar>صِيْدَ عَلَيْهِ يَوْمَاْنِ</ar>
         <free>Two days[nom] were-hunted upon-it</free>
         <alt><ed>It</ed> was-hunted upon it for two days</alt>
      </text>
      <igt>
         <t>
            <ar>صِيْدَ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>عَلَيْهِ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
           <ar>يَوْمَاْنِ</ar>
           <xlit>yawmāni</xlit>
           <en>two-days</en>
         </t>
      </igt>
      <sidecomment>
        “Upon-it”: on a road, or possibly on a mount?
        Days are not literally hunted, so this is figurative
        language.
      </sidecomment>
   </dictum>
   <dictum id="٠٩٣٣٨">
      <text>
         <ar>وُلِدَ لَهُ سِتُّوْنَ عَاْمًا</ar>
         <free>Sixty[nom] were born to him in years[acc]</free>
         <alt>He is sixty years old</alt>
      </text>
      <igt>
         <t>
            <ar>وُلِدَ</ar>
            <xlit>wulida</xlit>
            <en>was-born</en>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>لَهُ</ar>
         </t>
         <t>
           <ar>سِتُّوْنَ</ar>
           <xlit>sitt<inflw/>na</xlit>
           <en>sixty</en>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>عَاْمًا</ar>
         </t>
      </igt>
      <sidecomment>
        A metaphor, since years are not literally born.
        Here <ar>عَاْمًا</ar> is responsive to the question
        “sixty of what kind?” just as <ar>دِرْهَمًا</ar>
        in <ar>عِشْرُوْنَ دِرْهَمًا</ar> “twenty dirhams”
        answers “twenty of what kind?”
      </sidecomment>
   </dictum>
   <dictum id="٧٧٢٥٨">
      <text>
